sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2156103
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part is the complete combination of the Lux's A, B, G, C, D, E. This construct is meant to produce Bioluminescence, with the LuxAB beginning the structure, LuxG removing energy pathways to make the reaction more efficient, and LuxCDE synthesizing necessary substrates for the reaction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The addition of RBS and promoter to the construct.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mikhail Lujan and Carolina Sofia Gonzalez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2156017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Lux ABG with promoter and RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iGEM Glasgow, GenBank (see in each part)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LuxABG is a combination of the separate LuxA, LuxB and LuxG parts, including the relevant Ribosome Binding Site (BBa_K1725301) and an Anderson Promoter (BBa_K823005). LuxAB is the required pair for an operational lux, with LuxG decreasing the energy required for bioluminescence. LuxC and Lux D are needed to synthesize and replenish the aldehyde substrate needed for bioluminescence. This was synthesized by IDT (Integrated DNA Technologies).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Requires LuxCD to be fully functional
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carolina Sofia Gonzalez and Mikhail Lujan

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LuxBG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LuxBG is a combination of the separate LuxB and LuxG parts, including the relevant Ribosome Binding Site (BBa_K1725301) and the official iGem prefix and suffix. This part is listed as an intermediate because it requires LuxA for functional bioluminescence. LuxAB is the required pair for an operational lux, with LuxG decreasing the energy required for bioluminescence. This was synthesized by IDT (Integrated DNA Technologies).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The addition of a Ribosome Binding Site, prefixes, and suffixes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Carolina Sofia Gonzalez and Mikhail Lujan
